&lt;p&gt;Advert&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FIXED TERM CONTRACT / SECONDMENT OPPORTUNITY &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you passionate about improving the quality of care delivery, redesigning care pathways and developing best nursing practice for our patients in East Suffolk &amp; North Essex.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Following a successful bid for funding , we will be launching our &#39;Promoting Continence&#39; programme to undertake a full review of how we assess, manage and onward refer patients in our care who experience issues with incontinence during their stay with us.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role will lead the project working with community continence services, practice educators, patients, carers and wider stakeholders to drive significant improvements in how we manage continence across our organisation. The programme will drive changes in clinical assessment, nursing practice, product type/use and look to address the significant impact that incontinence can have on quality of life and emotional well-being. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post will form part of our Harm Free portfolio and report into the Heads of Harm Free Care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based on the Colchester site but with travel to other locations across NE Essex and Suffolk we want to recruit a clinical leader with experience at band 6/7 who is looking to gain project management and quality improvement experience on a project that will have a significant impact on our care delivery.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For internal applicants this maybe offered as a secondment opportunity and for external applicants as a fixed term contract unless secondment arrangements can be agreed with your current employer.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‘Please note that this role is subject to a DBS check which will be charged to the successful candidate. Full details can be found within the ‘DBS Information’ documents attached to this advert.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLisa SutherlandJob titleHarm Free Care LeadEmail addresslisa.sutherland@esneft.nhs.ukTelephone number07864 966489Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne Field - Harm Free Care Lead - joanne.field@esneft.nhs.uk - 07795686716&lt;/p&gt;
